  <p> <b style="text-align:center"> Definitions for SFDC – Relationship Suite   </b> </p>

  <p> <b> <u> Authorizers:  (Executives and Decision Makers) </u> </b> </p>
  
  <p> The individuals who have budget responsibility for this area, financial expenditure authority for this size or type of purchase, or have the position or title designating such formal authority.  Their signature is typically needed for finalizing or advancing a decision. </p> <br></br>
  
  <p> <b> <u> Influencers:  (Political Influencers and Consultants) </u> </b> </p>
  
  <p> The individuals to whom others look for endorsement and “buy-off” prior to completing and/or advancing projects and initiatives.  Individuals whose opinion is respected or from whom others take direction. </p> <br></br>
  
  <p> <b> <u> Justifiers:  (Financial Buyers and Subject Matter Experts) </u> </b> </p>  
  <p> The individuals who will ultimately need to rationalize, either financially or strategically, an investment of our products/services.</p> <br></br>
  
  <p> <b> <u> Operationalizers:  (End Users and Internal Enablers) </u> </b> </p>  
  <p>The individuals who have the final responsibility for implementing, using and leveraging the products and services we sell.</p> <br></br>
  
  
